# Mobile (phone) design scope

- **Target viewport:** Phones only — assume ~320px–430px width (e.g. iPhone SE to iPhone 14 Pro Max). Do **not** design or optimize for tablet (768px+) in the edits you make.
- **Breakpoints:** Base (unprefixed) Tailwind styles = phone. Use `sm:` (640px) and above only for optional enhancements, not for core layout or content. Treat `md:` (768px) and up as out of scope for this phase.
- **Existing project:** `app/globals.css` already uses `@media (max-width: 767px)` for mobile typography scaling (`--mobile-text-ratio`). Keep touch targets ≥44px, single-column layouts, and compact spacing appropriate for small screens.
- When adding or changing components, prioritize: thumb-friendly tap areas, readable text without zoom, minimal horizontal scroll, and stacking (flex-col) by default.
